name: OYO 922 Pp Dream Guest House
address: Jl. Pura Segara Penimbangan No.7x, Banyuasri, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81116, Indonesia
review 1:
The staff is super super super friendly and they take care of all of your needs.
The rooms are quite good for Asian standards, the bed is comfy, no bugs or anything, quite good shower, nice little balcony. The bathroom could have been a bit more clean, but no problem.
I would recommend to stay here, you really get to know the best Balinese hospitality!
review 2:
OYO 922 PP dream Penimbangan is very uncomfortable, worst place ever, and it has unsatisfactory service.
The pictures posted on OYO, and other accomodation providers are completely different. The pictures can tell everything about the horrible place
May this concern finds you well so there will not be same case in the future booking.
Consider your choice!

Thanks
review 3: Worth 5 stars. Room is cozy with great lighting, a balcony to smoke, clean bed and bathroom, hot water and towel is provided. The staff is very nice. Highly recommended üëçüèª
review 4: Nice room n clean, AC, frige, 3 storey, wi-fi facility,  good view to the sea n padi rice fields. Room rate varies due to seasonal ; starting from 350K - 500K excl. Bfast.
review 5:
Okay. It is clean and tidy but the food is Not that good.
the way to beach is short
The view from kitchen is nice even from the rooms...
It is ok for a Short time and Backpacker but not for long term holliday

name: Krisna's Beach Street Bar & Resto
address: Jl. Yeh Mumbul, Baktiseraga, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81119, Indonesia
review 1: Good food.. Good view... One of the best place in this sorrounding beach
review 2: Wow factor overlooking the oceanon one side and mountains on the other. FANtastic decor and funky vibe. Staff were super fun even joining in our impromptu dance session while waiting for friends to arrive. Food was great as were the cocktails. There is a stage for live music on Friday Saturday and Mondays.
review 3: Sympatic restaurant in 2 levels facing the sea...Simple menue card between traditional dishes and international treats...Didnt find the fare exagerated.
review 4:
Vibrant beachside bar, good for enjoying sunset while sipping cocktail. There are some karaoke rooms here.

The food, especially Indonesian and Balinese food are super delicious, strong, spicy and flavorful, like what locals prefer. Can be overwhelming for foreigner though. Price is reasonable and the service is very nice.
review 5: Good space for garden party, or beach party. Located in Pantai Penimbangan, one of famous and favourite place in Singaraja. Arroud the restaurant you can find so many food stalls to enjoy grilled corn.

name: RedDoorz near Penimbangan Beach Singaraja
address: Jl. A. Yani No.188, Baktiseraga, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81119, Indonesia
review 1: I have been stay here n its nice place
review 2: Bed sheet seems has not been changed for quite sometime

name: Warung PP Ikan Bakar
address: Baktiseraga, Buleleng, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81119, Indonesia
review 1:
The fish, recommend by the owner, was so tough and tasteless that we had to send it back.
When the bill came, they not only charged us for the full fish but also charged us 175k for shrimp (also very poor quality) that was on the menu for 30k (see picture).
When we asked the owner he became aggressive, shouting at us and frightening our 8 year old son.
After a long time he adjusted the bill telling us to never come back again. Advice we will surely follow.
Horrible experience
review 2: Found this place based on the great reviews, so had to try it. Great little place. Seafood is very nice. Had tigerprawns and mahi2 and love the way they prepared it. Will definitely come back!
review 3:
Very good service.
Very delicious
The best food in Balin
Really recommend
review 4: A really nice place with a very relaxed atmosphere. Very friendly staff. In addition to my meal, I saw various dishes at neighboring tables, all of which looked excellent. My fish was extremely good, as were the vegetables. Since I'm staying in Lovina for some time, I will definitely go there a few more times. Highly Recommended.
review 5:
The fish is absolutely amazing. Atmosphere easy and friendly.
We will surely back more and more.

name: Syobak Babi Khe-Lok
address: Jl. A. Yani No.290 B, Baktiseraga, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81116, Indonesia
review 1: Legendary syobak in Singaraja. This is the branch of the old city centre shop - run by the madame. Closer from Lovina and easier parking. Very tasty and spicy, unlike those in Java.  We love it. The contents are super complete, just ask for mixed with everything...
review 2:
This pork dish is definitely a must try when you‚Äôre in Singaraja. They have been selling the siobak for 3-4 generations. They have a few branches in Singaraja and also in Denpasar.
The pork is tender and the sauce is O mi gawd.....the best of the best.
I always go to this restaurant everytime I visit Singaraja.
review 3: delicious original syobak. same with the first KHE LOK. they also offered bakut, satay, fried rice, meatball.
review 4: The food here is very nice, you can get mostly Chinese food here, especially Char Siu Bak with a recipe that modified to match a Singaraja people's taste. You should try this Siu Bak here
review 5: Khe - lok old style and very famous Siobak in Buleleng - Singaraja - Bali - fair price for Siobak with rich  and drink

address: Jl. Pantai Indah Gg. III No.18, Singaraja, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81119, Indonesia

good place for hangout and met your friend.
they have live music show on saturday. very good price for all menu.

address: Jl. Pura Segara Penimbangan, Baktiseraga, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81119, Indonesia
review 1: The seafood fried rice and sapo tofu are good. The service is ok, you can pay with QRIS or a debit card. Grilled squid is so so and the portion is small.
review 2: Food is okay, not bad. The place is spacious. There is live music but it was bad. It's located in an area where you need to pay a retribution to enter.
review 3: Nice location near the beach at north side of Bali, they serve many kinds of food, fish fried rice was one of favourite
review 4: Foods are good and not expensive, many table and many foods in menu
review 5: the view is good, the food is delicious. the price is affordable

name: Mister Crab
address: Jl. Pantai Penimbangan, Baktiseraga, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81117, Indonesia
review 1: Had the 200K menu to share between 2 people. The crab is very good, but I dont care as much for the mussels and the small lobster. Next time I will go just for the crabs.
review 2:
Amazing experience!
1. FRESH! You can see aquarium full of live shrimps, crabs, fish.
2. DELICIOUS! The sauce is very good, the boiled seafood is boiled to perfection.
3. GREAT SERVICE! All the workers help you a lot!
review 3: My husbands favorite meal in Bali (we were here for a month)! No frills, but very friendly staff and great prices. I‚Äôd recommend over ordering to fill you up if you are a westerner!!!
review 4: I love how they prepare the food. Taste really good. Reasonable price
review 5: Fresh and delicious seafood. Served communal style for sharing, just like it should be :)

name: KEDAI HOPE
address: Jl. Pantai Penimbangan No.timur, Baktiseraga, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81119, Indonesia
review 1:
Fantastic. Great food with local price and amazing view.
You should try Ikan bakar here(one portion for 200g 20k).
Their fruit juice is also with good quality. There is a kids zone too.
review 2: The sunset here is breathtaking, food also nice and cheap, ikan bakar very tasty, but it attracted so many bugs and flies which I hate a lot
review 3: Amazing relaxing place especially to have dinner and watch the sunset! Food was great, live music is excellent and the staff was super friendly! Definitely recommend!
review 4: Very nice!! So good. Mie goreng, Chicken sweet sour üëçüëçvery cheap, nice View!
review 5: Nice ambience especially for the sunset. The staff is friendly and there was really good live music when we visited. Unfortunately, even though the prices are pretty low, the portion size is small and quality could be a little bit bigger. But for a drink and the sunset and a nice atmosphere, this place is perfect!
